          "body": "52:7 is one of the most-quoted verses in the New Testament — Paul cites it at Romans 10:15 to ground the gospel preacher's vocation in Isaiah's herald. The verse's logic is precise: the messenger is beautiful not for who he is but for what he carries (*good news, peace, salvation, your God reigns*). The four nouns build to the chapter's central proclamation — *malakh elohayikh*, your God reigns. The reign is announced not in the future but in the present indicative, even while the captives still sit in Babylon. 52:10 extends the audience: Yahweh has bared His holy arm 'in the sight of all the nations, that all the ends of the earth may see the salvation of our God.' What begins as local restoration ends as global revelation — a trajectory Acts 1:8 traces with the same geography."
